metadata.title: Bell 206
aws::graph::propositions: Military Variants of the Bell 206 Helicopter
Bell 206AS is an export version of the Bell 206 for the Chilean Navy.
Bell CH-139 JetRanger is the Canadian military designation for the Bell 206B-3.
Hkp 6A is the Swedish Army designation for the Agusta-Bell 206A.
Hkp 6A units were manufactured in Italy.
21 Hkp 6A units were manufactured.
Hkp 6A helicopters were used as training helicopters.
Hkp 6A helicopters were used as liaison helicopters.
Hkp 6A helicopters were used as light transport helicopters.
Hkp 6A helicopters were used as scout helicopters.
Hkp 6A helicopters were used as anti-tank helicopters.
Hkp 6A helicopters were armed with Anti-Tank Guided Missiles (ATGMs).
Hkp 6B is the Swedish Navy designation for the Agusta-Bell 206A.
10 Hkp 6B units were manufactured in Italy.
Hkp 6B helicopters were used as anti-submarine helicopters.
Hkp 6B helicopters were armed with depth charges.
Hkp 6B helicopters were equipped with emergency inflatable floats.
OH-58 Kiowa is a light observation helicopter.
OH-58 Kiowa replaced the OH-6A Cayuse helicopter.
TH-57A Sea Ranger consists of 40 commercial Bell 206A aircraft.
TH-57A Sea Ranger aircraft were purchased as the primary U.S. Navy helicopter trainer in January 1968.
TH-57A Sea Ranger aircraft were used for training prospective U.S. Navy personnel.
TH-57A Sea Ranger aircraft were used for training prospective U.S. Marine Corps personnel.

text:
### Military
Bell 206AS
Export version for the Chilean Navy.

Bell CH-139 JetRanger
Canadian military designation for the Bell 206B-3.
Hkp 6A
Swedish Army designation for the Agusta-Bell 206A. 21 units manufactured in Italy, used as training, liaison, light transport, scout and anti-tank helicopters armed with ATGMs.
Hkp 6B
Swedish Navy designation for the Agusta-Bell 206A. 10 units manufactured in Italy, used as anti-submarine helicopters, armed with depth charges. This variant was equipped with emergency inflatable floats.
OH-58 Kiowa
Light observation helicopter that replaced the OH-6A Cayuse.
TH-57A Sea Ranger
40 commercial Bell 206A aircraft purchased as the primary U.S. Navy helicopter trainer in January 1968 for training prospective U.S. Navy, U.S. Marine Corps, U.S.
